Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.53,0:00:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that mansion\Nis right up this hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.13,0:00:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.89,0:00:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Roses, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.03,0:00:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like sleeping\Nbeauty's castle...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.09,0:02:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}My name is Anna.\NAnna Liebert.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.53,0:02:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good luck,\NMr. Great Detective!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.73,0:02:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She was worried that\Nsomething might happen to you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I feel the same way\Nabout you as your mother.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.18,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Anna...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.28,0:02:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you dreaming,\NDetective Suk?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.28,0:02:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunge...\NAn inspector with the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,BKA?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.22,0:02:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.49,0:03:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You can lie down.\NI didn't come here to arrest you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.84,0:03:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a pretty nice\Nhospital room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I arrived here by checking out\Nhospitals that were involved with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.34,0:03:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the former Czechoslovakian\Nsecret police under the old regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.31,0:03:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging by your treatment...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be pretty important to\Nthe Czechoslovakian secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.09,0:03:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.15,0:03:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I know everything about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.66,0:03:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that Inspector Zeman, who\Nhad close ties with the secret police,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.43,0:03:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was beaten to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that the Prague police chief and\Ntwo detectives were poisoned to death...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that the two detectives who\Nwere following you were found shot dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.31,0:03:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that you are being pursued\Nbecause you are an important witness...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.71,0:03:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In any of these incidents, if you were to\Nlook at just the circumstantial evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.82,0:03:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you're the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.19,0:04:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what about Grimmer, the tall\Nman who Inspector Zeman questioned
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.29,0:04:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the day before\Nhe was beaten to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Grimmer's also not the culprit!\NHe's not the sort of person to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.67,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.57,0:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know who the culprit is,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.05,0:04:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This wouldn't be happening\Nto me if I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been betrayed by\Nall sorts of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.49,0:04:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been made out to be the culprit\Nand the police are after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.56,0:04:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough ! I don't want to be\Nbetrayed by anyone anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.26,0:04:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a detective, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.17,0:04:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're a detective,\Nyou must dissect everything calmly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You must dig up the truth\Nas rationally as you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.51,0:04:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,even at the expense of\Ndestroying your own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to be\Nbetrayed anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.42,0:05:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,doubt the people you\Ndon't ever want to doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.30,0:05:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Who gave you permission\Nto see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.95,0:05:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me to your boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him I want to talk to him\Nabout the Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.89,0:05:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll make him\Nwant to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.86,0:05:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge of the BKA...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.00,0:05:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've looked up your identity\Nand your past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.60,0:05:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I also heard rumors\Nabout you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when the old regime\Nwas in force, Captain Lanke.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, you're essentially the leader\Nof the Czechoslovakian secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big position with quite a lot of\Ntrouble attached to it at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I envy the fact that you can\Ntake a long vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.82,0:06:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear that two years ago your forceful\Ninvestigation drove a man to suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the secretary\Nto Senator Boltzmann,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.93,0:06:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a candidate for the leadership\Nof the German Democratic Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.53,0:06:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to know how\Nto get ahead in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.70,0:06:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.01,0:06:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If you took a softer line and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,actually managed to conceal\Nyour activities during democratization,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you could have emerged as\Nthe secret president of this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fear that the people have\Nof you is now all but a mere illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.86,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You're smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.13,0:06:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're so smart,\Nwhat do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No. As you know,\NI'm on a long vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.37,0:07:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is partially for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.17,0:07:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For true fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.42,0:07:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know if a real demon was\Nborn from the illusion you created.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.42,0:07:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you be referring\Nto Red Rose Mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I went all over the place\Nto reach that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.67,0:07:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This author had many,\Nmany pseudonyms.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.71,0:07:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The author of {\i1}The Nameless Monster{\i0}\Nis Emile Scherbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.55,0:07:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived in an old building\Nin Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A company is renting\Nthat room at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.39,0:07:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Under another alias,\NKlaus Poppe,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was an old farm in the suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.22,0:07:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The farm has already\Nbeen destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.83,0:07:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Under another alias, Jakub Farobek,\Nwas a rental office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.76,0:08:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So. ..you've finally arrived.. .\Nat Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.37,0:08:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.84,0:08:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how hard I search,\NI can't find anything on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.28,0:08:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means that\Nhe's one of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He's with the former\NCzechoslovakian secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.16,0:08:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.74,0:08:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There is something I've been\Nconsciously trying to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to forget the existence\Nof that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it still\Nstands there untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The political criminals\Nwho were taken there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,all the researchers who were there,\Ndisappeared one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.77,0:09:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the reason for the wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.64,0:09:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.04,0:09:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I went inside the mansion\Nthe other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.78,0:09:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no sign of any human\Nentry. It was completely abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.39,0:09:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But the wall to the north\Non the second floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.12,0:09:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall was plastered over as if\Nto hastily seal something away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That wall...\NMay I break it down?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.21,0:09:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you afraid of,\NCaptain Lanke?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.08,0:09:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You might die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you get any closer to it, you\Nand I might end up seeing true fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.40,0:11:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.17,0:11:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That name\Nbrings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like milk or sugar\Nin your coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Black is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.78,0:12:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.25,0:12:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I never expected a Franz\NBonaparta fan to appear now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from Moravia Publishing\Nthat you, Mr. Zobak,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.15,0:12:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,were Mr. Bonaparta's editor\Nfor a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.26,0:12:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.49,0:12:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was in charge of him when he\Nwas using the pseudonym, Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.43,0:12:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know what\Nkind of person he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.27,0:12:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.31,0:12:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He came to this house to\Nmake work arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.05,0:12:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He sat right on\Nthat chair just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:12:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He often played with\Nmy daughter in the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.16,0:13:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time, my daughter\Nsaid something strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.03,0:13:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She said,\N"that man is scary."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.10,0:13:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter probably doesn't\Nremember that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.18,0:13:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he work for a government agency\Nduring that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.21,0:13:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably. I assumed that was the\Ncase when I was doing business with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.22,0:13:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But judging by his demeanor, the way\Nhe talked and the clothes he wore...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a mildness and elegance\Nthat was nothing like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.03,0:13:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the important figures\Nof the old regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.56,0:13:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta had\Na doctorate in psychiatry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.07,0:13:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He was also a psychologist.\NHis specialty was neurosurgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.74,0:13:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.64,0:13:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the last time\NI saw him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.11,0:13:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it was\Nthe summer of '81 or '82.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That day, he wandered to\Nmy house. He told me his new story.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he looked strangely sullen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.19,0:14:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,New story?\NWhat kind of story was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.33,0:14:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,A story where\Na monster falls in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was like a mix between {\i1}Beauty\Nand the Beast{\i0} and {\i1}Sleeping Beauty.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.31,0:14:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I rejected it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, at the door,\Njust as he was about to leave...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.78,0:14:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He turned and said,\N"then what about this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"A story about a door that\Nshould never be opened."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.19,0:14:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him whether there was\Nparadise on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.73,0:14:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or whether a monster\Nwould come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.33,0:14:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "No. It should never be opened,\Nso I guess it's not much of a story."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.64,0:14:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He laughed as\Nhe said that and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.71,0:14:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last time\NI saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.79,0:15:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he tell you anything important\Nabout Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.66,0:15:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Nothing important.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.89,0:15:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer,\Nwhat were you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.30,0:15:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking that\Nit sure is a nice day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.27,0:15:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.18,0:15:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.18,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello? Is this the police?\NMy name is Zoback at Schweig Court.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A man just came to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.62,0:15:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he's a prime suspect in a multiple\Nhomicide that happened in Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.49,0:15:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He's Japanese.\NThe neurosurgeon, Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ethanol...\Nthe smell of disinfectant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.24,0:16:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Death? How many?\NHow many people died here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.88,0:16:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten... Twenty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.28,0:16:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No. More.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.67,0:17:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That woman...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.14,0:17:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman from\Nthe sketchbook...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.81,0:17:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The mother of the twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't hurry, the older students\Nwill take the soccer field!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.49,0:17:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up, Milosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Counter attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.83,0:17:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.53,0:17:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand back!\NThe goal's wide open!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.00,0:17:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They got us!\NThey got a goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.31,0:17:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.44,0:17:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Milosh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.91,0:17:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself,\NMilosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.98,0:17:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice defense,\NMilosh!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.78,0:17:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice clear!\NYou protected the goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.56,0:18:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That laugh...\NHe's all right now, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.50,0:18:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think,\NDr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.63,0:18:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer, aren't you going to\Nsee Milosh and the other children?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.01,0:18:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized why\NI wasn't good at soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.42,0:18:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think will\Nhappen to Detective Suk?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.86,0:18:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He's wanted as a prime suspect\Nin a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.40,0:18:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He's pretty much done-for,\Nsocially speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.60,0:18:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he turns himself in,\Nhow will he prove his innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.51,0:18:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How will he prove\Nthat there was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.91,0:18:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a blonde woman leaving\Nthe crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.05,0:18:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Suk is in the same situation as you.\NExcept for one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.89,0:19:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is goodbye, Doctor Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.42,0:19:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.86,0:19:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one person who knows the\Ndetails about the latest string of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.77,0:19:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of sending\Nthis to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.98,0:19:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letter from\Nthe serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.42,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I reveal in detail secrets that\Nonly the murderer would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.06,0:19:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But if you send this\Nto the police, you'll be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.33,0:19:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Grimmer will suddenly\Nreturn to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The police will cast a dragnet,\Nbut Grimmer will get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.11,0:19:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because he used to\Nbe a skilled spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.84,0:19:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll be a suspect and be forced\Nto run away for the rest of your life!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.48,0:19:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.02,0:20:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the person known as\NGrimmer never existed to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.42,0:20:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone just gave\Nthat role to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.66,0:20:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Grimmer is a suspect for the\Nrest of his life, I'll be completely fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.67,0:20:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.67,0:20:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of\Nthis method, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. No.\NThat's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.84,0:20:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to the Rose Mansion,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.38,0:20:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.51,0:20:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be close\Nto your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.22,0:20:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.59,0:20:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd tell you to not do anything rash,\Nbut you won't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.56,0:20:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But please don't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.77,0:20:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Grimmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.67,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That promise we made when\Nwe crossed the Czech border...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:20:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we meet again,\Nlet's have a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.44,0:21:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll fish for trout in surrounded\Nby wonderful scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.35,0:21:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have good wine\Nand cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Until we meet again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.40,0:21:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on I have to live\Nin fear of that sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.52,0:21:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.59,0:21:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.62,0:21:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\NLet me take a look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.30,0:21:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.46,0:21:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just apply some antiseptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.97,0:22:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Owowow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.97,0:22:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a boy, aren't you?\NBear with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.68,0:22:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. You're a strong boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.42,0:22:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Kenzo Tenma,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the police !\NCome with us to the station.
